    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220\u00b0C/ 200\u00b0C (fan)/ 425\u00b0F/ Gas 7</p><p>Top, tail and\u00a0slice\u00a0the<strong>\u00a0carrots</strong>\u00a0at an angle</p><p>Add the\u00a0<strong>carrots</strong>\u00a0to a\u00a0baking tray, drizzle them with\u00a0<strong>olive oil</strong>\u00a0and season them with a pinch of\u00a0<strong>salt</strong>\u00a0and\u00a0<strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Add the<strong> pigs in blankets</strong> to the tray and put everything\u00a0in the oven for 20 min or until the sausages are cooked through</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/bangers-in-blankets-with-figgy-gravy/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>While the carrots and sausages are cooking, boil a kettle</p><p>Peel and finely slice the<strong>\u00a0red onion<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong></p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a knob of<strong>\u00a0butter</strong>\u00a0over a very low heat</p><p>Once hot, add the<strong>\u00a0sliced red\u00a0onion</strong>\u00a0with a pinch of\u00a0<strong>salt\u00a0</strong>and cook for 8 min or until softened and caramelised</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/bangers-in-blankets-with-figgy-gravy/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, cut the\u00a0<strong>potatoes</strong>\u00a0(skins on) into small bite-sized pieces</p><p>Tip: If you'd\u00a0rather skin-off mash, peel the potatoes first</p><p>Add the\u00a0<strong>potatoes</strong>\u00a0to a pot of\u00a0<strong>boiling water\u00a0</strong>with a pinch of\u00a0<strong>salt\u00a0</strong>over a high heat and cook for 10-12 min or until fork-tender</p><p>Once cooked, drain and\u00a0return to the pot to steam dry</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/bangers-in-blankets-with-figgy-gravy/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Re-boil a kettle</p><p>Dissolve the<strong>\u00a0Kallo\u00a0beef stock cube<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span> </strong>in 250ml\u00a0<span class=\"text-danger\">[400ml]\u00a0</span><strong>boiled water</strong>, add the <strong>fig relish</strong>\u00a0and mix until fully combined \u2013 this is your<strong>\u00a0figgy stock</strong></p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/bangers-in-blankets-with-figgy-gravy/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once caramelised, add 1 tsp<span class=\"text-danger\">\u00a0[2 tsp]\u00a0</span><strong>flour\u00a0</strong>to the onion and cook for 1 min, stirring until they're evenly coated in the flour</p><p>Add the <strong>figgy stock</strong>, increase the heat to medium\u00a0and cook for 7-8 min or until thickened to a gravy-like consistency \u2013 this is your<strong> figgy gravy</strong></p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/bangers-in-blankets-with-figgy-gravy/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>While the gravy thickens, add\u00a0the<strong>\u00a0green beans</strong>\u00a0to a pot with plenty of\u00a0<strong>boiling water\u00a0</strong>and a pinch of<strong>\u00a0salt\u00a0</strong>and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, cook for 3-4 min or until tender with a bite</p><p>Once cooked, drain and return to the pot and keep covered until serving</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/bangers-in-blankets-with-figgy-gravy/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>While your\u00a0green beans are boiling, return\u00a0the<strong>\u00a0drained\u00a0potatoes\u00a0</strong>to a low heat and add a splash of\u00a0<strong>milk</strong>\u00a0and a knob of\u00a0<strong>butter</strong></p><p>Season with a pinch of\u00a0<strong>salt\u00a0</strong>and\u00a0<strong>pepper</strong>\u00a0and mash until smooth</p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/bangers-in-blankets-with-figgy-gravy/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>pigs in blankets</strong> over the\u00a0<strong>mash</strong>\u00a0with the\u00a0<strong>carrots</strong>\u00a0and\u00a0<strong>green beans</strong>\u00a0to the side</p><p>Pour the <strong>figgy gravy</strong>\u00a0all over and enjoy!</p><p><strong>Feel like you've seen me before? You have! I'm an Everyday Favourite with a Christmas twist.</strong></p>",
            "order": 8
        }
